      "message": "[Critical] Line 660: 🔴 Critical Issues - The new controller starts at its hard-coded default `initialBitrateKbps` of 800 Kbps and `setLimits()` only clamps it; it is never synchronized with `videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent`. On the first RR update, calls may force the encoder toward 800 Kbps even when the negotiated/current codec bitrate is different. Initialize or reset the controller from the current codec bitrate after `setupVideoBitrateInfo()`.\n\n```suggestion\n        bwController_.setLimits(codecVideo-\u003eminBitrate, codecVideo-\u003emaxBitrate);\n        bwController_.setTargetBitrate(videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent);\n```",
