      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T07:43:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 823: 🔴 Critical Issues - `delayMonitor()` now sends a REMB packet on every overuse/normal callback, removing the previous 500ms/1s throttling. This callback can run at RTP-packet frequency, so this can flood RTCP, waste bandwidth/CPU, and make the remote encoder oscillate. Keep rate limiting around both decrease and increase feedback.\n\n```suggestion\n    auto now \u003d clock::now();\n    if (bwState \u003d\u003d BandwidthUsage::bwOverusing) {\n        if (now - last_REMB_dec_ \u003c DELAY_AFTER_REMB_DEC)\n            return;\n        last_REMB_dec_ \u003d now;\n        JAMI_LOG(\"[BandwidthCtrl] Reception overuse detected, sending REMB decrease\");\n        auto v \u003d cc-\u003ecreateREMB(0x6803);\n        socketPair_-\u003ewriteData(v.data(), static_cast\u003cint\u003e(v.size()));\n    } else if (bwState \u003d\u003d BandwidthUsage::bwNormal) {\n        if (now - last_REMB_inc_ \u003c DELAY_AFTER_REMB_INC)\n            return;\n        last_REMB_inc_ \u003d now;\n        auto v \u003d cc-\u003ecreateREMB(0x7378);\n        socketPair_-\u003ewriteData(v.data(), static_cast\u003cint\u003e(v.size()));\n    }\n```",
